[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hey everyone, I\'m Ming product manager for Collab LCC. Over the past 2 years we\'ve watched 3D Gaussian Splatting take off across the 3D industry. More and more people are using it to capture [music] the real world and it really does look stunning. But as we got to playing to'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actual projects, we hit [music] a catch. It looks great but it isn\'t always easy to work with. You [music] can\'t add in models, can\'t change up the scenes, the files getting bigger and bigger, spread across a handful of complicated tools.'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You can show it off but bringing it into [music] a real workflow is hard. So we asked ourselves, if 3D Gaussian Splatting is going to be truly usable, what\'s still missing? &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; That\'s exactly why we built LCC 2.0, the'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'first world model editor. Now let\'s get into the good stuff. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Back in the 2D era, image editors and'

[01:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video editors changed how [music] we make content. So the spatial intelligence era deserves an editor of its own, one built for world models. That\'s what we set out to build [music] at LCC, an all-in-one world model editing workflow. First up, LCC model'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'editor. It\'s the first 3DGS editor with synchronized multi LOD editing. It doesn\'t adjust added Gaussian points but entire spatial structure. You can crop, clone, [music]'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'separate, recolor and added collision bodies within a world model. Clearing clutter out of a scene, [music] duplicating an element, building a brand new space. It all happens right here [music] in editor. And here\'s what matters most. Every change, every slice'

[02:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you make [music] carries through automatically. From foreground to background, from desktop to mobile, [music] every level of detail updates at once. On desktop, the LCC model editor handles'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'unlimited [music] scale 3D Gaussian editing for serious professional work. And on the web version, you can [music] add spatial models of up to 20 million points right in your browser. With that [music] same synchronized multi-LOD'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'editing, fast and nothing to install. If LCC model editor reshapes [music] the world model itself, LCC scene editor is what brings it into actual business needs. Add annotations, set up interactive logic, build a spatial fly-throughs,'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] manage your assets, and you are shaping the entire spatial experience. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Together, this turns our statistic 3D Gaussian model into something interactive, operational, and multimedia-rich. [music]'

[02:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A genuine world model. Side by side, the model editor and the scene editor [music] cover the full pipeline. From processing the model to deploying the scene. That\'s what finally makes the [music] world model a'

[03:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'manageable, reusable digital asset. Now, you might be wondering, &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; how does an unlimited scale Gaussian model load smoothly and stay accessible at the same time? [music]'

[03:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The answer is our all new LCC2. LCC2 isn\'t just a format [music] upgrade. It\'s a data organization architecture designed specifically for world models. Earlier 3D Gaussian formats [music] captured an image. LCC2 starts to'

[03:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'express the space. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Beyond the Gaussian data itself, LCC2 stores collision, geometry, depth, and [music] other spatial information. With all of that, a 3D Gaussian isn\'t for human eyes only. Now, computers, AI'

[03:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'algorithms, and robots &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; can understand it, too. That\'s what makes it a true world model. So, how [music] do we keep all this growing data loading and editing efficiently? First, the data structure. [music]'

[03:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'LCC2 splits huge data sets into blocks, each with its own [music] position and detail level, dispatching only the data you need. Outlines load [music] first from the distance. Detail fills in as you move closer. Next, LCC2 introduced [music] a'

[04:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dual-track LOD mechanism. The real-time track keeps huge scenes loading smoothly. The training track handles the fidelity, [music] sharpening detail as you moving close.'

[04:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In short, LCC2 stays high quality and lightweight at once. [music] From a small room to a sprawling campus, it streams smoothly even on a weak connection and everyday devices. And here\'s a big one. Even without original'

[04:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'capture data, [music] your existing PLY or LCC files convert straight into LCC2. So, everything you already built gets [music] a second life. Here\'s something we\'ve always believed.'

[04:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '[music] A world model\'s real value isn\'t in building it. It\'s in moving it between tools. We want LCC2 to become the USB ports of the spatial [music] intelligence era. One shared connection that lets different devices, software,'

[05:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and apps all [music] speak the same language. For one model to move freely between systems, we designed LCC2.0 from day one to import and added LCC formats [music] like PLY, SPZ, and SLD. And to'

[05:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'convert smoothly to and [music] from LCC2. As an open-source format, LCC2 is fully documented and open to developers. LCC2 has already been integrated into a long [music] list of leading global'

[05:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ecosystem partners, spanning digital twins, spatial computing, film [music] and TV, XR, robotics, and AI. So, what\'s models can shine [music] on different platforms. On top of giving [music] professional'

[05:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'users more production power, we also lower the barrier to entry for 3D Gaussian Splatting creation. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Now a single video is all it takes to automatically reconstruct a 3D Gaussian Splatting, people, and small objects. Pair those with large complex [music]'

[05:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'scenes you capture using Aspired devices, and whole new range of world model creation opens up. LCC2 isn\'t about prettier models. It\'s about turning 3D [music] Gaussian Splatting from something you display into a world'

[06:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'model you produce, edit, [music] share, and deploy. A 3D model you can edit like video, manage like a data set, and share as freely as anything on the internet. The full LCC2 suite is [music] live now. Download it or try it online at'

[06:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'aspired.com, and tell us what you think. See you next time. [music]'
